The paper discusses the evaluation of vision-based driving models, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of offline metrics and validation datasets, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the correlation between offline evaluation and driving quality, which is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
